<HL>
   Marketing Brief -- Sherwin-Williams Co.:
   New National Ad Campaign
   Aimed at Do-It-Yourselfers
</HL>
<DATE>
05/24/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   SHW
</CO>
<LP>
   Sherwin-Williams Co. will launch a $10.4 million
nationwide ad campaign aimed at the do-it-yourself market.
   The home-improvement company will begin soon television
and radio commercials in addition to 48 ads in home
decorating magazines.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Part of the thrust of the campaign is to convince
consumers that Sherwin-Williams is a home-decorating
consultant as well as a retailer, said Karl Schmitt, director
of advertising. The company will be offering color-planning
guides at its 1,900 stores to help do-it-yourselfers develop
color schemes.
</TEXT>
